1
00:00:11,750 --> 00:00:13,680
Audacity tips
Opening a sound track:

2
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:16,980
On the menu, click on file, then on open.

3
00:00:16,980 --> 00:00:19,850
(shortcut: control + O).

4
00:00:19,850 --> 00:00:24,029
Browse for your sound file and click on open.

5
00:00:24,029 --> 00:00:30,630
Importing a sound track:
On the menu, click on file, then on import

6
00:00:30,630 --> 00:00:35,880
(shortcut: shift + control + I), then on audio.

7
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:42,090
Browse for your sound file and click on open.

8
00:00:42,090 --> 00:00:49,040
Cutting a sound track:
On the menu, click on the selection tool (shortcut:

9
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:50,730
key F1).

10
00:00:50,730 --> 00:00:56,129
Click on the sound file you want to edit and
drag the mouse to create a section to cut.

11
00:00:56,129 --> 00:01:06,220
Then click on cut (shortcut: key Ctrl + X).

12
00:01:06,220 --> 00:01:13,689
Moving a sound file in the timeline:
On the menu, click on the time shift tool

13
00:01:13,689 --> 00:01:17,130
(shortcut: key F5).

14
00:01:17,130 --> 00:01:29,390
Click on the sound file you want to edit,
and move it in the timeline.

15
00:01:29,390 --> 00:01:38,350
Fading in and out:
On the menu, click on the selection tool.

16
00:01:38,350 --> 00:01:43,340
Click on the sound file you want to edit and
drag the mouse to highlight a section to cut.

17
00:01:43,340 --> 00:02:10,750
Then, click on effect and fade out.

18
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:20,080
Amplifying a sound track:
Choose the track you want to amplify.

19
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:24,379
Click and drag on the track and highlight
the part you want to amplify.

20
00:02:24,379 --> 00:02:48,170
Then, on the menu, click on effect and amplify,
and choose the quantity needed.

21
00:02:48,170 --> 00:02:55,690
Exporting the final track:
On the menu, click on file, then on export

22
00:02:55,690 --> 00:02:59,280
(shortcut: control + E).

23
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:02,680
Choose the type of file you need and give
it a name.

24
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:06,190
Then, click on save and on ok.

25
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:13,110
You can include metadata tags (artist name,
track title, album title, track number, year,

26
00:03:13,110 --> 00:03:14,669
genre and comments).

